=== EXECUTIVE SUMMARY ===
## Executive Summary

On 2024-11-14, an unauthorized actor accessed the production database using compromised service account credentials (`svc-analytics`) that were accidentally exposed in a public GitHub repository, exfiltrating 12,400 user records containing names, email addresses, and bcrypt-hashed passwords over a 6.5-hour period. The breach stemmed from a team reorganization that inadvertently made a private repository public, exposing the credential (`Analyt1cs_2024!`) which was discovered by attackers 17 days later. Immediate remediation included rotating all service account credentials, enforcing MFA for database access, deploying GitHub secret scanning, notifying affected users, and filing regulatory breach notifications. A scheduled penetration test will provide additional security validation.
